<body>

<header>
    <div class = "navContainer">

        <div class="logo">
            <i class="fas fa-project-diagram"></i>
            <span>Algorithms</span>
        </div>

        <div class = "navLinks">
            <a href="https://github.com/Josink/Sinkaiye-CS203-F25-G6-Project2-Website" target="_blank"><i class="fab fa-github"></i> GitHub</a>
            <a href="/algorithms"><i class="fas fa-sort-amount-down"></i> Algorithms</a>
        </div>

        <% if (user){ %>
            <div class = "authenticationButton">
                <a href="/" class="btn btn-outline">Home</a>
                <a href="/logout" class="btn btn-primary">Log out</a>
            </div>
        <% } else{ %>
            <div class = "authenticationButton">
                <a href="/" class="btn btn-outline">Home</a>
                <a href="/signup" class="btn btn-primary">Sign Up</a>
            </div>
        <% } %>

    </div>

</header>

<main>

    <div class = container>
        <div class = title>
            <h1>ALGORITHMS</h1>
        </div>

        <p>
            This website collects implementations of the standard sorting algorithms
            <span class = highlight>(Selection, Bubble, Insertion, Merge, Quick, Heap)</span>
            and searching algorithms
            <span class = highlight>(Sequential, Binary)</span>.
            The program runs each algorithm on controlled inputs (random, sorted
            ascending) records comparisons, swaps/movements, and runtime, and outputs CSV
            data for analysis.
        </p>

        <div class = subtitle>
            <h2>Sorting Algorithms</h2>
        </div>

        <div class = algInfo>
            <h2>
                Selection Sort
            </h2>
            <p>
                Selection Sort repeatedly scans the unsorted portion of the array,
                selects the smallest element, and swaps it into its correct position.
                It always performs the same number of comparisons regardless of input
                order.
            </p>

            <h3>
                Time Complexity:
            </h3>

            <ul>
                <li>Best: O(n²)</li>
                <li>Average: O(n²)</li>
                <li>Worst: O(n²)</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                Basic operations: comparisons + swaps
            </p>

        </div>

        <div class = algInfo>
            <h2>
                Bubble Sort
            </h2>
            <p>
                Bubble Sort repeatedly compares adjacent elements and swaps
                them if out of order. Optimized versions stop early if no swap
                occurs in a pass.
            </p>

            <h3>
                Time Complexity:
            </h3>

            <ul>
                <li>Best: O(n)</li>
                <li>Average: O(n²)</li>
                <li>Worst: O(n²)</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                Basic operations: comparisons + swaps
            </p>

        </div>

        <div class = algInfo>
            <h2>
                Insertion Sort
            </h2>
            <p>
                Insertion Sort grows a sorted list by inserting one element
                at a time into its correct position.
            </p>

            <h3>
                Time Complexity:
            </h3>

            <ul>
                <li>Best: O(n)</li>
                <li>Average: O(n²)</li>
                <li>Worst: O(n²)</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                Basic operations: comparisons + swaps
            </p>

        </div>

        <div class = algInfo>
            <h2>
                Merge Sort
            </h2>
            <p>
                Merge Sort uses the divide-and-conquer strategy:
                split the array, recursively sort subarrays, and merge them
            </p>

            <h3>
                Time Complexity:
            </h3>

            <ul>
                <li>Best: O(nlogn)</li>
                <li>Average: O(nlogn)</li>
                <li>Worst: O(nlogn)</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                Basic operations: comparisons + swaps
            </p>

        </div>

        <div class = algInfo>
            <h2>
                Quick Sort
            </h2>
            <p>
                Quick Sort partitions the array around a
                pivot, then recursively sorts the left and right halves.
            </p>

            <h3>
                Time Complexity:
            </h3>

            <ul>
                <li>Best: O(nlogn)</li>
                <li>Average: O(nlogn)</li>
                <li>Worst: O(n²)</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                Basic operations: comparisons + swaps
            </p>

        </div>

        <div class = algInfo>
            <h2>
                Heap Sort
            </h2>
            <p>
                Heap Sort builds a max heap and repeatedly extracts the maximum element.
            </p>

            <h3>
                Time Complexity:
            </h3>

            <ul>
                <li>Best: O(nlogn)</li>
                <li>Average: O(nlogn)</li>
                <li>Worst: O(nlogn)</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                Basic operations: comparisons + swaps
            </p>

        </div>

        <div class = subtitle>
            <h2>Searching Algorithms</h2>
        </div>

        <div class = algInfo>
            <h2>
                Sequential Search
            </h2>
            <p>
                Sequential Search scans each element until the target is found or the end is reached.
            </p>

            <h3>
                Time Complexity:
            </h3>

            <ul>
                <li>Best: O(1)</li>
                <li>Average: O(n)</li>
                <li>Worst: O(n)</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                Basic operations: comparison
            </p>

        </div>

        <div class = algInfo>
            <h2>
                Binary Search
            </h2>
            <p>
                Binary Search repeatedly divides the search interval in half. Requires input to be sorted.
            </p>

            <h3>
                Time Complexity:
            </h3>

            <ul>
                <li>Best: O(1)</li>
                <li>Average: O(log n)</li>
                <li>Worst: O(log n)</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                Basic operations: comparisons
            </p>

        </div>

    </div>

</main>

